<p>
<seg id=1> The International Court of Justice in Hague judged three defendants for their war crime against Serbs in Bosnia, but announced their high commander not guilty. </seg>
<seg id=2> The International Court adjudicated that it was not necessary for Bosnia Muslim Filarichi to take responsibility for his underling's violence against Serbian war prisoners in Cailaibichi prison camp in 1992. </seg>
<seg id=3> Other three defendants were sentenced for fixed-term imprisonment for their action in so called terroristic rule in the prison camp. </seg>
</p>
